  "local_port": 49984,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "Linking your valid Aadhaar card to your State Bank of India (SBI) account is a straightforward process that can be completed through various methods, including online, via SMS, using the SBI mobile app, or by visiting a branch. Below are detailed steps for each method:\n\n---\n\n### **Method 1: Linking Aadhaar via SBI Net Banking**\n\n1. **Log In to Net Banking:**\n   - Visit the [SBI Net Banking portal](https://www.onlinesbi.com/) and log in using your Customer ID and password.\n\n2. **Navigate to Profile Settings:**\n   - Once logged in, go to the **\"Profile Settings\"** section. This is usually found under the **\"My Accounts\"** or **\"Services\"** tab.\n\n3. **Select Aadhaar Linking:**\n   - Look for an option labeled **\"Link Aadhaar\"** or similar.\n\n4. **Enter Aadhaar Details:**\n   - Input your 12-digit Aadhaar number.\n   - Enter the last four digits of your mobile number registered with Aadhaar for OTP verification.\n\n5. **Verify and Submit:**\n   - Confirm that all details are accurate.\n   - Submit the information. An OTP will be sent to your registered mobile number for verification.\n\n6. **Confirmation:**\n   - Upon successful verification, you will receive a confirmation message indicating that your Aadhaar has been linked to your SBI account.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 2: Linking Aadhaar via SMS**\n\n1. **Ensure Mobile Number Registration:**\n   - Make sure that your mobile number is both registered with your SBI account and linked to your Aadhaar.\n\n2. **Compose the SMS:**\n   - Draft an SMS in the following format:\n     ```\n     UID <space> your 12-digit Aadhaar number\n     ```\n     *Example:*\n     ```\n     UID 123456789012\n     ```\n\n3. **Send the SMS:**\n   - Send this SMS to **567678** or the latest designated SBI number for Aadhaar linking (it's advisable to check the current number on the [SBI official website](https://www.onlinesbi.com/)).\n\n4. **Receive Confirmation:**\n   - You will receive an SMS confirming the successful linking of your Aadhaar to your SBI account.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 3: Linking Aadhaar via SBI Mobile Banking App (YONO or SBI Anywhere)**\n\n1. **Download and Open the App:**\n   - If you haven't already, download the **SBI YONO** or **SBI Anywhere** app from the [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=in.sbi.sbionlineapp) or [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/in/app/yono-sbi/id1281177562).\n   - Log in using your credentials.\n\n2. **Access Profile Settings:**\n   - Navigate to the **\"Profile\"** or **\"Settings\"** section within the app.\n\n3. **Select Aadhaar Linking Option:**\n   - Find and select the **\"Link Aadhaar\"** option.\n\n4. **Enter Aadhaar Information:**\n   - Input your 12-digit Aadhaar number as prompted.\n\n5. **Verify Details:**\n   - The app may use OTP verification sent to your registered mobile number linked with Aadhaar.\n\n6. **Submit and Confirm:**\n   - Submit the details. A confirmation notification will appear once the linking is successful.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 4: Linking Aadhaar by Visiting an SBI Branch**\n\n1. **Find Your Nearest Branch:**\n   - Locate the nearest SBI branch using the [SBI Branch Locator](https://www.onlinesbi.com/branch-atm-locator.html) on their official website.\n\n2. **Prepare Necessary Documents:**\n   - Carry your valid Aadhaar card.\n   - Bring your SBI passbook or account details for reference.\n\n3. **Fill Out the Aadhaar Linking Form:**\n   - Upon arrival, request the Aadhaar linking form from the bank officer.\n   - Fill in the required details accurately.\n\n4. **Submit the Form and Documents:**\n   - Hand over the completed form along with your Aadhaar card and any other required documents to the bank officer.\n\n5. **Verification and Confirmation:**\n   - The bank will process your request. You will receive a confirmation via SMS or email once your Aadhaar is successfully linked to your SBI account.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Considerations:**\n\n- **Ensure Accuracy:** Make sure that the name, date of birth, and other personal details on your Aadhaar card match those in your SBI account to avoid discrepancies.\n\n- **Update Mobile Number:** Your mobile number linked with Aadhaar should be active and the one registered with your SBI account to receive OTPs for verification.\n\n- **Data Privacy:** SBI adheres to strict data privacy norms. Your Aadhaar information will be used solely for verification and linking purposes.\n\n- **Current Regulations:** As per the latest regulations (as of October 2023), linking Aadhaar to bank accounts is not mandatory but is beneficial for seamless banking services and compliance with KYC norms.\n\n---\n\nBy following any of the above methods, you can easily link your Aadhaar card to your SBI account. If you encounter any issues or require assistance, it's recommended to contact SBI's customer support or visit your nearest branch for personalized help.",
